{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_012aLCazQcDQUgFYY9NECfDe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have all the information needed. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### 1. New file: `config/monitoring/prometheus-rule.yaml`\n\nCreate the directory `config/monitoring/` and this file:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: PrometheusRule\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    control-plane: controller-manager\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheusrule\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: monitoring\n    app.kubernetes.io/created-by: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: kustomize\n  name: alerting-rules\n  namespace: system\nspec:\n  groups:\n    - name: multiarch-tuning-operator.rules\n      rules:\n        - alert: MultiarchImageInspectionFailureRateCritical\n          expr: |\n            (\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[10m])\n              /\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[10m])\n            ) > 0.05\n          for: 5m\n          labels:\n            severity: critical\n          annotations:\n            message: >-\n              Image inspection failure rate has exceeded 5% over the last 10 minutes.\n              Affected pods may be stuck in SchedulingGated state or relying on\n              fallback architecture assignment. Check registry connectivity and\n              pull secret configuration.\n```\n\n### 2. New file: `config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- prometheus-rule.yaml\n```\n\n### 3. Modified file: `config/default/kustomization.yaml`\n\nAdd `../monitoring` to the `resources` list so the PrometheusRule is included in the default kustomize overlay:\n\n```diff\n resources:\n - ../crd\n - ../rbac\n - ../manager\n - ../webhook\n+- ../monitoring\n```\n\n### Commands to run\n\n```bash\n# Create the directory\nmkdir -p config/monitoring\n\n# After creating the files above, verify the kustomize build works:\nkustomize build config/default\n```\n\nNo `make` targets need modification — the kustomization overlay picks up the new resource automatically.\n\n---\n\n### Design rationale\n\n- **Metrics used**: `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` (counter) and `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` (counter) — both defined in `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go:58-69`.\n- **Threshold**: `> 0.05` (5%) matches the SLO boundary documented in `agentic/RELIABILITY.md:117` (\"ImageInspectionFailureRateHigh\" at 5% critical).\n- **Window**: `[10m]` rate window matches the alerting PromQL example in `agentic/RELIABILITY.md:67-71`.\n- **`for: 5m`**: Prevents transient spikes from paging; the condition must persist for 5 minutes before firing.\n- **Labels**: Follow the same `app.kubernetes.io/*` labeling scheme as the existing `ServiceMonitor` in `config/prometheus/monitor.yaml`.\n- **Namespace `system`**: Uses the kustomize placeholder namespace, which gets rewritten to `openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator` by the `namespace:` field in `config/default/kustomization.yaml`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":148,"cache_creation_input_tokens":275,"cache_read_input_tokens":41628,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":275,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b3cc91c8-acb5-429c-b921-ef720feff74e","uuid":"f1849194-f024-4b55-83fa-b74e4cee12f8","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:50:53.865Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDjUVKx7dfj3rKs1tDa5"}
